rovides an examination unprecedented in scope and scale of changes in academia. The authors document the changing emphases accorded the branches of learning, the applied and basic divisions, and the disciplinary fields. They find deep transformations, as anticipated, but offer a new explanation for these shifts. Changes in academic focus are less the work of outside interest groups, but instead are cultural maps to the altering features of globally institutionalized understandings of reality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aEDUCATION / Organizations & Institutions.2bisacsh1 aGabler, Jay, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMeyer, John W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362585340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503625853423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503625853/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles